Github Steps:
Create New Repository with some Name
https://github.com/Rajanarender/Selfstudy.git //copy this URl
go to linux terminal
enter the command for cloning/download the repository: git clone https://github.com/Rajanarender/Selfstudy.git
Now we need to switch to this git directory Selfstudy

cd directoryname[here Selfstudy] ,Do the below steps in the cloned directory only
enter the command: git init
enter command: git branch --to check if any branch/folder is present or not

git checkout -b branchName [To create Git branch with some name] //Compulsory

cp -R Study Selfstudy[copy your local folder to git]
like this cp -R ../Study .

=>git add Study[directory or filename] -- this will add directory/file to the index
git status --this will display all the files of that directory
git commit -m "Selfstudy directory added to Git on 6June2018" [commit the directory with "discription"]
git push origin brachName [this will push the local repository to git server/website]
Enter Username:Rajanarender
Password:

Now goto website
=>Your Profile to see your new Repository

------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to download/clone this Repository to your local system??
Go to your profile in website
Select the Repository
Click the "Clone or Download"[Green colored] button
Select and copy the https URL
Now open your linux terminal
enter the command for cloning/download the repository to local: git clone https://github.com/Rajanarender/Selfstudy.git
(Or) Directly download the ZIP file to yout local

********************************************************************************************************
git pull origin branchname [This is used for getting the modified file in git website to your already created repository]

If we want to update modified/New files of your local to git website,then follow this steps
=>git add filename
=>git status [to check modified/new files]
=>git commit -m "Message explaining the file changes"
=>git branch[This will display the current working branch]
=>git push origin branchname[ Use tab to display all the branches available]
